{
  "stem": "945.4",
  "chunk_idx": 0,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 6.2,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And so we started our life in the little ghetto, that was to be our home for another couple of years.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "This was the summer of 1942.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "My dad and my brother Joe were the first ones to venture out into the countryside, and they were lucky enough that they found a Ukrainian lady who was a doctor veterinarian.",
      "word_count": 32
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And she started giving my dad and my brother odd jobs around her place-- chopping wood and working on the-- on the potato patch and--",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Yes, it was, of course, very dangerous to do that.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "But like I said we were a little-- or my dad was and I was-- we were little more comfortable because we could speak the language and we weren't afraid to be out in the countryside and to do work on, on gardening, and all that kind of stuff.",
      "word_count": 49
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "I don't know.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I, I don't think so, because it went on for some time.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And she was very glad that my dad and my brother Joe were doing the work for her.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And maybe she was the kind of person that tried to help us out as well.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "She might have been from those Ukrainians that were feeling sorry for us and tried to help us.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "They were given food while they were working and maybe something to take home, a half a loaf of bread, a few potatoes, anything.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Food was starting to get a little scarce because as time went on the Ukrainian population wasn't as willing to come into town because word spread that there was disease spreading in the ghetto.",
      "word_count": 34
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And--",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "I call it a ghetto because it was a area that was surrounded, populated, overpopulated with Jewish people.",
      "word_count": 18
    }
  ],
